WEBVTT

00:00.031 --> 00:04.818
these samples in the video description for sure.

00:05.660 --> 00:07.162
So I think we've gone over everything.

00:07.442 --> 00:15.114
The generator starts off with text, puts that into normalized text, calculates hidden features right here.

00:15.475 --> 00:27.253
These hidden features on one hand are used to predict the lengths of each of the tokens in the sound and are also used as an input to the generator here.

00:27.233 --> 00:42.833
Now they can only be used as an input to the generator if the generator knows how to align them in time and how to align them in time is predicted from these predicted lengths right here via this aligner algorithm.

00:43.314 --> 00:45.757
The lengths are the only thing that is predicted.

00:46.238 --> 00:48.260
Everything then is deterministic.

00:48.661 --> 00:55.890
The aligner is simply a Gaussian kernel over the predicted locations on the

00:55.870 --> 01:04.205
on the time axis, so the Gaussian kernel is to make this alignment a bit fuzzy, to make this prediction fuzzy.

01:04.786 --> 01:11.859
You perform a weighted sum with these features and then the generator knows where to put the tokens.

01:12.360 --> 01:18.030
Finally, the generator can upsample the now aligned tokens into sound.

01:18.010 --> 01:20.213
This goes into the discriminator.

01:20.514 --> 01:31.970
The discriminator is actually five different discriminators, which each try to discriminate the generated from the real at different time scales.

01:32.892 --> 01:44.929
In addition to that, you have a discriminator on the spectrograms, and you also have an L1 loss on the spectrograms, which helps especially at the beginning of training.

01:44.909 --> 02:09.297
For the L1 loss of the spectrograms, you have to again compute an alignment, but you do this in a deterministic way by this thing down here, this dynamic time warping where you simply assume that they are aligned and forgive them for not being aligned with a soft penalty and not a hard zero score.

02:10.306 --> 02:11.731
All right, this was the paper.

02:11.992 --> 02:17.871
Again, if you like this, leave a like, a comment, share it out, subscribe and have a good day.

02:18.092 --> 02:18.493
Bye-bye.

